content.description: Start above the miniature choss cave with a very cool left hold and move on up. A sds to this would be very cool. There's also a possible variation just the left of this that could go up the mungy crack (read: needs to be cleaned) and would be a bit more difficult, but somewhat contrived. Come on out and climb it dudes!
content.location: To the right of Pitocin on the lower wall. Roughly in the middle.

content.description: Pretty mellow warmup. A lot taller than the picture shows. This follows good holds on a crack that comes to a stance. Continue up the crack on an angled slab or exit right. Left looks kinda sketch and somewhat dirty.
content.location: First of the easier climbs from the left, next to Bananimals.

content.description: Possum starts off the climbing on the lower wall. Kind of a one move wonder, and like so many climbs in Duluth, ends in a slopey topout.
content.location: Furthest left problem on the lower wall.

content.description: A good V1 to induce your climbing experience at the PPW. Follow the dirty crack to the right of St. Luke's.
content.location: In between St. Luke's and St. Mary's on the lower wall.

content.description: This fun climb looks harder than it is. The wall blanks out for a bried moment here and "Midwives" is the result. Slabby face climbing.
content.location: Just to the right of the easier climbs, next to St. Mary's.

content.description: A neat little crack that requires some finger-lockage and few reachy moves. I thought stand start was V3. The sit start variation begins on a good undercling and requires a little more desperation, so V4
content.location: Next climb to the right of Possum, up the good crack, left side of the lower wall. (2nd problem from the left).

content.description: I gave this a climbing rating because of it's length and grade. Super mellow, but pretty high. Still nothing to worry about.
content.location: Next available climb to the right of Midwives.

content.description: Bananimals is a terric crimpfest with a deadpoint balance crux. I would give it 4 stars if it was a bit longer. Awesome jug for the last move. The sds has yet to be done and might add a number to the grade.
content.location: 3rd route in from the left on the lower wall, next to "Get the Epidural." Blank looking face.

content.description: This wall faces the road. The good stuff is on the 50 foot long face until it gets a bit chossy the further one goes to the right and uphill towards the upper wall.
